                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1041</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 559</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 983
                    of April 6, 1927, with regard to a monopoly for the sale of sulphur, saltpetre
                    and other chemicals which has been established by the Chinese authorities at
                    Canton.</p>
                <p>The Department is of the opinion that no further action need be taken in this
                    matter for the present.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph C. Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
